result.execSummary:
The defendant Jesse Ml Foss was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Criminal Damage to Property [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.01(1).
  • Criminal Damage to Property [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.01(1).
  • Criminal Trespass to Dwelling [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.14.
  • Theft-Movable Property <=$2500 [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.20(1)(a).
  • Theft-Movable Property <=$2500, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.20(1)(a).

records.addlTxt: Cover Letter from Court to Atty's

Defendant Jesse Ml Foss in court with attorney David Susens.  Defendant Jesse Ml Foss in custody.  Kevin R. Calkins appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Court states case and State states appearances.  Parties rec/rev revocation summary.  State makes recommendations.  Atty Susens responds.  DE makes brief statement.  Court admonishes DE and sentences.  State requests civil judgments.  Atty Susens requests joint and several continue.  Court orders civil judgments.

Cts 1 - 5:
9 months jail w/huber concurrent to each other but consecutive to any other sentence
126 days credit to be applied
All unpaid costs/surcharges/restitution to be converted to civil judgments
Sentencing hearing on revocation on February 16, 2017 at 09:30 am.

Defendant Jesse Ml Foss in court with attorney Adam Raabe.  Defendant Jesse Ml Foss in custody.  Kevin R. Calkins appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Court states case and State states appearances and that parties have come to agreement as to the amount of restitution.  State notes co-actors were all juveniles.  Only thing to be addressed is the DE's ability to pay.  Atty Raabe agrees w/statements by State.  Atty Raabe calls the DE - S&T.  State does cross-exam.  Atty Raabe has no re-direct.  Court asks questions of DE.  Atty Raabe does re-direct.  No further testimony.  Atty Raabe makes argument re: inability to pay.  State makes argument.  Court finds there is or will be an ability to pay some and order $12,000.00 restitution be paid by DE.  Amended JOC to be done to reflect restitution amount of $12,000.00.
Restitution hearing on November 2, 2016 at 11:00 am.
Restitution hearing on October 14, 2016 at 11:15 am.
Scheduling conference on September 8, 2016 at 08:30 am.
Restitution hearing on July 21, 2016 at 09:00 am.

Defendant Jesse Ml Foss in court with attorney Adam Raabe.  Kevin R. Calkins appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  State states case and appearances and agreement.  Atty Raabe agrees and lists co-defendant's names.  Atty Raabe enters NC plea to all 5 counts.  DE agrees.  Court questions DE on pleas/accepts/finds guilty.  State makes statement.  Atty Raabe makes statement.  Court admonishes DE and sentences.  Restitution hearing to be set for one hour.  

Cts 1-5:  NC to all counts

Probation for 36 months on each count concurrent to each other
Conditions of probation:
Costs/surcharges of $453.00 x 5 to be paid to Clerk of Court's Office TODAY or set up payment plan
DNA sample to be provided
Restitution to B.B. and any restitution surcharges to be paid J&S w/co-DE's (Restitution to be determined at a later date/restitution hearing)
Counseling per agent
No contact w/co-DE's or the victims of these offenses
(Co-DE's...T.R. dob 7/25/00, R.R. dob 7/6/01, M.W.R. dob 9/21/00, N.C. dob 11/25/00)
DE to report to P&P immediately upon leaving the courthouse today
Expungment if successful
Plea/sentencing hearing on May 9, 2016 at 10:00 am.
Status hearing on May 3, 2016 at 01:00 pm.

Defendant Jesse Ml Foss in court with attorney Adam Raabe.  Sue Mueller appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Attorney Raabe gives status.  Plea to Count 1-5.  1-4 as PTAC.  No further charging by State.  No Contest Plea entered, advised of constitutional rights, plea accepted by Court.  Attorney Raabe addresses and request it be known who the co defendants are.  State can not provide that at this time.  Matter to be rescheduled off the 1 p.m. calendar.  Restitution stipulation provided, however no surcharges added.  Guilty plea questionnaire filed.  


RECOMMENDATION:
Count 1-5:
36 months Probation
Submit DNA sample
Undergo any counseling per agent
AODA & treatment
Expungement upon successful completion of probation.
No contact with co defendants; 
$10680.54 Restitution with 10% Surcharge To:  (PAID THRU CLERK OF COURTS)  J/S with co defendants; 
$243.0 Fine/Costs, $200.00 DNA surcharge and $10.00 property crime surcharge for Count 1.  Count 2-5 is $243.00 costs, $200.00 DNA surcharge (PAID THRU CLERK OF COURTS) 
Paperwork handed in court.  Status hearing scheduled for May 3, 2016 at 01:00 pm.
Booking on or before 3/30/2016 and no contact w/alleged victims or their premises and must obey curfew.

Pre-trial conference at 03-04-2016 09:00 am.
Return date at 03-30-2016 01:00 pm.

DE appears in person w/Atty Adam Raabe.  State appears by Atty Sue Mueller.  Defendant waives reading of complaint.  File set for pre-trial conference/return date.  $1,000.00 signature bond set.  Special bond conditions as follows:  Booking on 3/30/2016 or 3/23/2016, must comply w/curfew and no contact w/co-DE's or alleged victims.
